== History == The [[Ottoman Empire]] (1299&ndash;1923), the predecessor of modern [[Turkey]] was one of the 17 signatories of the [[Metre Convention]] in 1875. For 58 years both the international and the traditional units were in use, but after the proclamation of the Turkish Republic, the traditional units became obsolete. In 1931 by Act No. 1782, international units became compulsory and the traditional units were banned from use starting 1 January 1933.<ref>''Türkiye’nin 75 yılı'', Tempo yayınları, İstanbul, 1998, p. 53</ref>
